		<title>Three years later, the console wars are more confusing than ever</title>
		<link>http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2016/12/three-years-later-the-console-wars-are-more-confusing-than-ever/</link>
		<pubDate>Fri, 23 Dec 2016 15:44:09 +0000</pubDate>
		<dc:creator><![CDATA[Kyle Orland]]></dc:creator>
				<category><![CDATA[Opposable Thumbs]]></category>
		<category><![CDATA[console wars]]></category>

		<guid isPermaLink="false">http://arstechnica.com/?p=1012553</guid>
		<description><![CDATA[We walk you through the changes upending the console market in 2016 and beyond.]]></description>
				<content:encoded><![CDATA[<div id="rss-wrap">
<figure class="intro-image intro-left"><img src="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/consolewars-800x450.jpg"><p class="caption" style="font-size:0.8em"><a href="https://cdn.arstechnica.net/wp-content/uploads/2016/12/consolewars.jpg" class="enlarge-link" data-height="450" data-width="800">Enlarge</a> (credit: <a rel="nofollow" class="caption-link" href="http://arstechnica.com/author/aurich-lawson/">Aurich Lawson</a>)</p>  </figure><div><a name="page-1"></a></div>
<p>Last year, after much <a href="http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2014/09/dispatches-from-the-console-war-revisiting-our-launch-day-impressions/">previous hemming</a> and <a href="http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2013/11/head-to-head-everything-you-need-to-know-in-the-ps4-vs-xbox-one-battle/">hawing</a>, we recommended that console gamers looking for a new console finally <a href="http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2015/12/dispatches-from-the-console-wars-xbox-one-vs-ps4-two-years-later/">take the plunge and invest in a PlayStation 4</a>. But the console market has changed in the 12 months since that recommendation, from the release of new generation-splitting hardware to the announcement of upcoming console hardware from both Microsoft and Nintendo.</p>
<p>Is it time to upgrade? Is it better to wait? Should you just stick to <a href="http://arstechnica.com/gaming/2016/12/one-upping-the-nes-classic-edition-with-the-raspberry-pi-3-and-retropie/">a retro-focused Raspberry Pi build</a> instead? Below, we'll walk you through the current state of the console market, summarize what we know about the near future, and give you our best recommendation for where to put your console dollars.</p>
<h2>Go Pro?</h2>
<p><a href="//player.cnevids.com/embed/58248dfffd2e615dac000008/5511d76261646d5566020000">The PS4 Pro: It's bigger, it's pricier, and it's more powerful. But does it offer a true 4K experience? Video hosted by: Mark Walton. (video link)</a></p>
